<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-2"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-2')">2</a>. Icy conditions across the lake force most ships to remain in port during late winter, and <em>Skipper's Folly</em> does likewise to maintain its cover as a commercial freighter. Typically, winter layup lasts from the second week of January until the middle of March.</div>
</div>

